    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Note that this works in the slightly more cumbersome call to\n`load_ipython_extension`, as demonstrated here :\nhttp://nbviewer.ipython.org/gist/arokem/46040963eea7d8db3d76\n\nOn Sat, Nov 8, 2014 at 11:50 AM, Steven Silvester notifications@github.com\nwrote:\n\n> Right now it has this signature:\n> \n> load_ext(module_str)\n> \n> ```\n> Load an IPython extension by its module name.\n> ```\n> \n> It would be nice to be able to add keyword arguments to be passed to the\n> underlying extension. For example, pymatbridge\n> https://github.com/arokem/python-matlab-bridge/blob/master/pymatbridge/matlab_magic.py#L68\n> accepts matlab as a keyword, being the path to the Matlab executable.\n> With this change, the user would be able to type: %load_ext pymatbridge\n> matlab=<path_to_matlab>.\n> \n> cc @arokem https://github.com/arokem\n> \n> —\n> Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHub\n> https://github.com/ipython/ipython/issues/6888.\n"
